Week 2 – Data Cleaning and Importance of Data Types

“In Week 2, we focused on data cleaning using Power Query.

Some of the tasks we performed were:

Changing column names

Changing data types

Removing null values

Removing error values

Changing the correct data type is very important.
If a column has the wrong data type, it can cause calculation errors.

For example, if numeric data is stored as text, Power BI cannot perform calculations like sum or average.
So we converted the columns into the correct data types such as text, number, and date to make the data ready for analysis.

For numeric missing values, we replaced them using statistical methods like mean or average.
